UNITED STATES of America v. Homer H. CLARK, Jr., Executor, Estate of Helen A. Clark, deceased. No. 7299. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. April 8, 1963. Louis F. Oberdorfer, Asst. Atty. Gen., and Lee A. Jackson, Atty., Tax Division, Dept, of Justice, Washington, D. C., and Lawrence M. Henry, U. S. Atty., Denver, Colo., for appellant. James H. Turner, Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed April 8, 1963, on motion of appellant. 209 F.Supp. 895.
